 The product of two positive integers minus their sum is 39.
Let one integer be $a$ and the other be $b$. The given condition can be written as
\begin{align*}ab - (a + b) = 39\end{align*}
This can be solved to get
\begin{align*}ab - a - b = 39\end{align*}
\begin{align*}ab - a - b - 39 = 0\end{align*}
\begin{align*}(a - 1)(b - 39) = 40\end{align*}
